                    "maxclass": "comment",
                    "numinlets": 1,
                    "numoutlets": 0,
                    "patching_rect": [ 35.0, 19.0, 600.0, 74.0 ],
                    "saved_attribute_attributes": {
                        "textcolor": {
                            "expression": "themecolor.theme_textcolor"
                        }
                    },
                    "text": "In this example we are creating a flurry of triggers from incoming onsets. Since there are triggers being generated by dk.triggerbounce~ already, we can use those sample triggers to trigger the analysis downstream by using dk.triggerframe~. This ensures that every generated trigger is accounted for and does not require a separate layer of onset detection. In this example, once the new frames are analyzed spectral and loudness compensation is applied to more closely match the filtered noise bursts."
                }
            },
